<module status="bronze">
  <h>a</h>
  <p>The particle <g>a</g> has a number of uses in Gaelic – <ul>
      <li>the elative preposition <a href="?gd=a^preposition"><g>à</g></a>
        <en>out of, from in</en></li>
      <li>the third person singular possessive determiner <a href="?gd=a^determiner"><g>a</g></a>
        <en>his, her, its</en></li>
      <li>the relative clause particle <a href="?gd=a^relative"><g>a</g></a>
        <en>who(m), which, that</en></li>
      <li>a reduced form of the illative preposition <a href="?gd=do^preposition"><g>do</g></a>
        <en>into</en></li>
      <li>[...]</li>
    </ul>
  </p>

